{"type":"text","timestamp":1773245720104,"sessionID":"ses_3225b067cffelwLK8Sy8mv6BSq","part":{"id":"prt_cddae387c00293gL3JlpGG8e4E","sessionID":"ses_3225b067cffelwLK8Sy8mv6BSq","messageID":"msg_cddae2975001Es2ffK3KcXo8Sb","type":"text","text":"All work is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished across both commits:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Commit 1 (`172127f`): Features subcommands\n- **`features check`** — Emits `{ok, items_checked, errors, warnings, issues}` in JSON mode\n- **`features archive`** — Emits `{archived, count}` / `{dry_run, archived, count}` in JSON mode\n\n### Commit 2 (`024de85`): All operational commands\n- **`status`** — Emits `{active, wave_id, agents, counts, total}` in JSON\n- **`launch`** — Dry-run emits structured selection; live emits wave creation state and suggests polling via `wombo status --output json`\n- **`verify`** — Emits `{verified, count, wave_id}` per agent in JSON\n- **`merge`** — Emits `{merged, count, failed, wave_id, pushed}` with per-branch results\n- **`cleanup`** — Dry-run and actual cleanup emit structured resource lists\n- **`retry`** — Dry-run and actual retry emit agent state in JSON\n- **`resume`** — Emits triage results and relaunch state in JSON\n- **`upgrade`** — Emits version check/install results in JSON; fixed `installVersion` to accept `fmt` parameter\n- **`index.ts`** — Passes `outputFmt: args.outputFmt` to all operational command option objects\n\n### Key design decisions:\n- Human-friendly text output remains the default\n- JSON schemas are consistent with existing features subcommand patterns using `output()`, `outputMessage()`, `outputError()`\n- Long-running commands (launch, resume) emit initial state in JSON mode and suggest polling `wombo status --output json` rather than entering monitoring loops\n- Typecheck and build both pass cleanly","time":{"start":1773245720103,"end":1773245720103}}}
