{"type":"text","timestamp":1773246851940,"sessionID":"ses_3224353feffeqylOxitWfk83Ra","part":{"id":"prt_cddbf6491002qgbrRt2rD246ej","sessionID":"ses_3224353feffeqylOxitWfk83Ra","messageID":"msg_cddbf5834001Y0RuLa7ZPsFIYC","type":"text","text":"Now I see the full picture. The monitoring loops in `resume.ts` (the headless branch at lines 305-405) have unguarded console.log calls at lines 319, 347, 353, 398, 405. However, looking at the flow:\n\n1. For interactive resume + JSON mode: the JSON is emitted at line 237, then it returns.  ✅\n2. For headless resume + JSON mode: there's no JSON emission before entering the monitoring loop! The code only handles the \"no agents to relaunch\" case (line 163-174) and the interactive mode (line 236-247) with JSON. The headless monitoring loop (line 252+) doesn't have JSON-mode early return.\n\nThis is the **same pattern** as `launch.ts` - the monitoring loop is inherently a long-running, interactive process. In `launch.ts`, the JSON is emitted at line 710 before entering the loop. But in `resume.ts`, for the headless case, there's no JSON output emitted before the monitoring loop.\n\nLet me check whether this is an issue that needs fixing. Looking at `resume.ts` line 182-184:\n\n```typescript\nif (fmt === \"text\") {\n    console.log(`\\nRe-launching ${toLaunchNow.length} agent(s)...\\n`);\n    printDashboard(state);\n}\n```\n\nThe text output before monitoring is guarded. But for JSON mode, there should be a structured JSON response emitted before the monitoring starts, similar to how `launch.ts` does it.\n\nThis is a genuine gap. Let me fix it, along with any other issues I've identified. Let me also review the `resume.ts` flow once more to identify all JSON mode issues:\n\nThe resume headless JSON mode issues:\n1. Line 319, 347: `console.log(...)` in SIGINT/onQuit handlers — these are edge cases during shutdown, acceptable\n2. Line 353: `console.log(\"(--no-tui mode, dashboard prints every 15s)\\n\")` — unguarded\n3. Line 398: `printDashboard(state)` — prints even in JSON mode \n4. Line 405: `console.log(\"Wave complete.\")` — unguarded\n5. Missing JSON response before entering monitoring loop\n\nSimilarly for `launch.ts`:\n1. Line 440: `console.log(...)` — unguarded in monitoring (but JSON already emitted)\n2. Line 460, 463: `console.log(...)` — unguarded (but JSON already emitted)\n3. Line 523: `printDashboard(state)` — unguarded\n4. Line 530: `console.log(\"Wave complete.\")` — unguarded\n5. Line 551, 607-613: `console.log(...)` — unguarded in interactive mode (but JSON emitted)\n\nThese are real issues for JSON consumers who might pipe the output. Even though JSON was already emitted, additional text would corrupt JSON piping. Let me fix all these.","time":{"start":1773246851939,"end":1773246851939}}}
